        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-core): index memory path in FTS text for filename queries (fixes #94102)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes #94102.\n- `memory_search` FTS rows indexed only chunk body text, so queries for date-like filename stems (e.g. `2026-06-17-1649`) returned unrelated files with `textScore: 0` even when the target file was indexed and content search worked.\n- Include the memory file path in the FTS `text` column at index time (`${entry.path}\\n${chunk.text}`) so filename/date tokens participate in hybrid keyword ranking.\n- Vector embeddings and chunk body text are unchanged.\n- Keyword-search snippets and lexical density scoring strip the indexed path prefix back off, so excerpts show the chunk body (not the path line) and stay consistent with vector-search snippets; the FTS index keeps the path purely for matching.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: Exact filename/date-token queries fail to rank the matching memory file first despite a clean index and working content search.\n- Real environment tested: Linux (WSL2) source checkout, Node 22, FTS-only memory backend (`provider: none`, vector disabled).\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. Built the local checkout (`pnpm build`).\n  2. Ran a redacted behavior probe that indexes two memory files and executes `memory_search` for `2026-06-17-1649` through the bundled memory-core runtime.\n- Evidence after fix:\n  Terminal transcript:\n  ```text\n  $ node behavior-probe-memory-filename.mjs\n  {\n    \"top\": [\n      {\n        \"path\": \"memory/2026-06-17-1649.md\",\n        \"textScore\": 0.000003905989965114915,\n        \"score\": 1\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n  ```\n\n  Snippet-cleanliness guard (run via `node`), asserting the keyword hit returns the chunk body and not the `memory/...` path line:\n\n  ```text\n  $ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-search.test.ts\n  ✓ searchKeyword filename token ranking (issue #94102) > matches date-like filename stems when path is included in FTS indexed text\n    expect(results[0].snippet).toBe(\"Token has been expired or revoked Google OAuth Testing mode\")\n    expect(results[0].snippet.startsWith(\"memory/\")).toBe(false)\n  Tests  23 passed (23)\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: Top result path is `memory/2026-06-17-1649.md` with `textScore > 0`; nearby file `memory/2026-06-17-1701.md` is not returned for the filename stem query. The returned snippet for that hit is the chunk body (`Token has been expired or revoked Google OAuth Testing mode`), not the path-prefixed FTS text.\n- What was not tested: Live `openclaw memory search` with Gemini embeddings against a production workspace (requires provider credentials and reindex).\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-search.test.ts` — 23 passed.\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:extensions` — exit 0.\n- Regression coverage: filename/date stem ranks first with `textScore > 0`, and the keyword snippet equals the chunk body (asserts it does not start with the `memory/` path prefix).\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? Yes\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? No\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No\nHighest-risk area:\nHybrid memory search keyword ranking for existing indexes\nMitigation:\nChange applies on reindex/write paths only; no config surface. Existing indexes need reindex to pick up path tokens in FTS text.\n\n## Current review state\n\nNext action:\nAwait CI + ClawSweeper review\nWaiting on:\nMaintainer review\nBot comments addressed:\nUpdated Real behavior proof after initial mock-only-proof gate failure\n\nAI-assisted: yes\n\n",
